sql:
SELECT DISTINCT a.application_name, a.application_category_name 
FROM applications a
INNER JOIN network_traffic nt ON a.application_name = nt.application_name;

SELECT application_name, application_category_name, SQRT(AVG(bidirectional_packets)) AS sqrt_avg_packets
FROM network_traffic
GROUP BY application_name, application_category_name;

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_id, u.user_name, u.email, u.role
FROM users u
INNER JOIN network_traffic_reports r ON u.user_id = r.user_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_entries
FROM network_traffic
WHERE duration < (SELECT AVG(duration) FROM network_traffic);

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM network_traffic 
WHERE bidirectional_packets > 1000;

external_knowledge:
- "voyagers sailing the digital seas" refers to the users generating network traffic;
- "time of embarkation" corresponds to the timestamp of the network traffic entry;
- "harbors they set sail from" refers to the source IP addresses;
- "guessed ships" refers to the applications whose names and categories are guessed;
- "confidence in the vessel's identity" corresponds to `application_confidence`, which must be greater than 0.95;
- "latest voyage" indicates sorting by timestamp in descending order.

sql:
SELECT nt.*, a.application_name 
FROM network_traffic nt 
LEFT JOIN applications a ON nt.application_name = a.application_name;

SELECT network_traffic.application_name, applications.application_category_name 
FROM network_traffic
INNER JOIN applications ON network_traffic.application_name = applications.application_name;

SELECT application_name, application_confidence, bidirectional_packets, bidirectional_bytes 
FROM network_traffic 
WHERE application_confidence = (SELECT MAX(application_confidence) FROM network_traffic);

external_knowledge:
Shining stars - Active users with recent network traffic;
Journeys through the digital forest - Applications generating network traffic;
Clarity of these paths - Confidence level of guessed applications;
The most recent journeys - The most recent network traffic entry for each user-application combination.

sql:
SELECT application_name 
FROM applications 
WHERE application_name NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT application_name FROM network_traffic);

SELECT application_name, COUNT(DISTINCT source_ip) AS unique_source_ip_count
FROM network_traffic
GROUP BY application_name;

SELECT application_name, SUM(bidirectional_packets) AS total_packets
FROM network_traffic
GROUP BY application_name;
